A wild storm hits Scotland, northern England and Northern Ireland leaving up to 14,000 people without power in western Scotland. (Reuters via ABC News)British Airways Flight 2276, a Boeing 777 aircraft, suffers an uncontained engine failure and fire on take-off from McCarran International Airport, Las Vegas, Nevada, United States. Fourteen of the 172 on board are injured and taken to a nearby hospital. (BBC), (NBC News)